timeline_data.body: @jasonkatonica pls take a look. This is from 0.48 M1 testing.

This test should be ignored once the two remaining PRs for the windows ignore lists are merged into Java 17 and 11:

Windows specific list on 17:
- https://github.com/ibmruntimes/openj9-openjdk-jdk17/pull/376

Windows specific list on 11:
- https://github.com/ibmruntimes/openj9-openjdk-jdk11/pull/821

I did validate that the FIPS libraries load OK by manually using the [builds found here for the M1 .48 release](https://hyc-runtimes-jenkins.swg-devops.com/job/build-scripts/job/openjdk17-pipeline/1047/artifact/target/windows/x64/openj9/) to ensure this is not the same issue we ran into with  https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/issues/19986 where the libraries were completely missing.
The jdk17 exclude list is merged now, and also included in the v0.48.0-release branch.

comments_data.body: @jasonkatonica pls take a look. This is from 0.48 M1 testing.

This test should be ignored once the two remaining PRs for the windows ignore lists are merged into Java 17 and 11:

Windows specific list on 17:
- https://github.com/ibmruntimes/openj9-openjdk-jdk17/pull/376

Windows specific list on 11:
- https://github.com/ibmruntimes/openj9-openjdk-jdk11/pull/821

I did validate that the FIPS libraries load OK by manually using the [builds found here for the M1 .48 release](https://hyc-runtimes-jenkins.swg-devops.com/job/build-scripts/job/openjdk17-pipeline/1047/artifact/target/windows/x64/openj9/) to ensure this is not the same issue we ran into with  https://github.com/eclipse-openj9/openj9/issues/19986 where the libraries were completely missing.
The jdk17 exclude list is merged now, and also included in the v0.48.0-release branch.
